title: For Trade:  Howard Hill "Big Five" longbow $375
postcontent:
Howard Hill (November 13, 1899 - February 4, 1975) was an archer who was unofficially referred to as the "World's Greatest Archer". He is the only person to win 196 archery field tournaments in succession. 

The Howard Hill Company of Hamilton, Montana, is and has been offering Hill-style longbows for many years. The particular model which I have for sale was their top-of-the-line Big Five model. The Big Five,
according to the literature and information given by Mrs. Betty Ekin, friend of Howard Hill and, along with son Craig, operator of the Howard Hill Archery Company, was patterned after the famous “Sweetheart” Hill's favorite bow.  The construction of ths bow is constructed of laminated bamboo per Hill’s design. Hill reportedly took a trip to Japan in 1960 in order to find and ship home a specific species of bamboo he found most suitable for his needs, and I understand that the Hill Company still uses this species in the
bow’s construction to date. The belly and face of the Big Five bow are both backed by glass.
The bow that I am offering was made in 1974 (one year before Mr. Hill passed away) and is set up for 70 lbs. at a 29" draw length. The bow itself is 70 inches long. Because it was custom made for me it sports..."Custom made for My Name". This is painted on and could be easily removed. I used the bow to hunt whitetail for a few years so there are some superficial scratches (nothing deep). I would recommend having a bowyer make a new string as the one I have is frayed in places.

The picture posted looks identical but is not a pic of mine. I can send pics is you're seriously interested.
